From 4240f84679108340d2f610a1403973d749844203 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Sumitkumar Pandit <hello@codedbysumit.com>
Date: Tue, 7 Jul 2026 06:17:40 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 2/2] feat(v2): colorful sub-pages + Brevo screenshots section
 + 3 new blog posts + sitemap

Colorful consistency across all sub-pages (previously only home was colorful):
- /email-hub: 6-color icon rotation on 12 topic cards + gradient CTA
- /free-tools: emerald/purple/amber/cyan icon tiles + colored badges
- /templates: rainbow category chips + colored icon-per-card
- /resources: colored icon tiles + colored type badges
- /blog: rainbow category badges (each post gets its own accent) + gradient featured card
- /portfolio: colorful Services icons, Certifications icons, gradient primary CTAs
- All hero eyebrow chips now use badge-{color} tinted pills

Brevo screenshots section (previously commented out with obvious placeholders):
- Restored as 'From My Brevo Dashboard' section in TOC
- 4 labelled tiles: dashboard, template editor, sending stats, automation
- Drop-in ready: place files at /public/brevo/{dashboard,template-editor,sending-stats,automation}.png
- Until real files exist, tiles render an intentional-looking colored gradient
  with sparkle icon and 'Real screenshot coming - updated after each UI refresh' copy
  (safer than obvious 'Screenshot placeholder 1' text)
- Onboard hint at bottom shows the exact upload path for maintenance

Three new deep-dive blog posts (11 -> 14 posts, backs up '14+ Guides' hero claim):
- 'Brevo Transactional vs Marketing Email' - pipeline separation, code sample
- 'The 12-Point HTML Email Testing Checklist' - Outlook survival, dark mode
- 'Brevo Webhooks + Event Tracking' - Next.js webhook route, idempotency

SEO enhancements:
- sitemap.js now includes /about-author, /privacy-policy, /terms, /affiliate-disclosure
- openGraph blocks added to /email-hub, /free-tools, /resources
- Hero stats corrected: '12 In-Depth Guides' -> '14+ In-Depth Guides', '4 Free Tools' -> '5 Free Tools'
- About-Author page & trust pillar updated to match new numbers
